<body>
    <h1>Task 25 - Researching AWS Architecture and Designing an Open-Source=
 On-Prem Alternative</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"edc57cf6b262">&nbsp;</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"1c33e00708f3" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-1.ExecutiveSummary">1. Executive Summ=
ary</h1>
<p local-id=3D"5dc7cea3058e">This document presents a comprehensive researc=
h study of Dhan, a real-world high-frequency trading (HFT) and retail broke=
rage platform built on AWS. It covers the platform's AWS architecture, iden=
tifies the core cloud services used, and proposes an equivalent on-premise =
architecture built entirely with open-source tools.</p>
<p local-id=3D"db49f4e3ea2e">The goal is to give ABC Technologies a clear u=
nderstanding of how production-grade financial trading systems are built =
=E2=80=94 both in the cloud and on-premise =E2=80=94 and to evaluate the tr=
ade-offs between the two approaches.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7edf55edadbc">&nbsp;</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"eeca9d0c480a" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-2.AboutDhan=E2=80=94TheSelectedApplic=
ation">2. About Dhan =E2=80=94 The Selected Application</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"039184595bb9" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-2.1WhatisDhan?">2.1 What is Dhan?</h2=
>
<p local-id=3D"963a8efccc70">Dhan is an Indian retail brokerage and trading=
 platform that enables users to trade equities, derivatives, currencies, an=
d commodities on NSE (National Stock Exchange) and BSE. It is known for ult=
ra-low latency order execution, advanced charting, algorithmic trading APIs=
, and a mobile-first UX.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"b415819eb4ff" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-2.2KeyCharacteristics">2.2 Key Charac=
teristics</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"2204ec2e5048">
<li local-id=3D"b51be79ed125">
<p local-id=3D"f7a979854fda">High-frequency order processing (thousands of =
orders per second)</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"c165c7b28951">
<li local-id=3D"647630c4da1e">
<p local-id=3D"dbb6114ef88c">Sub-millisecond order routing to NSE/BSE via c=
o-location</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"de79cdd0b131">
<li local-id=3D"662e540e0eb5">
<p local-id=3D"2f5af392a6d0">Real-time risk checks, margin management, and =
P&amp;L calculations</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"27a8cae44bad">
<li local-id=3D"2035cdd727ef">
<p local-id=3D"b45f9120a138">Regulatory compliance with SEBI, CDSL, and exc=
hange mandates</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"459e5ae813df">
<li local-id=3D"c7f6b422bb78">
<p local-id=3D"25568bf919e0">Multi-channel: mobile app, web platform, algor=
ithmic trading API</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3f291d7812af">&nbsp;</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"6f20d4f7f02a" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-3.AWSArchitectureofDhan">3. AWS Archi=
tecture of Dhan</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"92240826513f" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-3.1High-LevelArchitectureOverview">3.=
1 High-Level Architecture Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"937d7a2cc065">Dhan's AWS infrastructure is organized within =
a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) optimized for low-latency trading. Traffic fl=
ows from users through Route 53 and API Gateway, into a private subnet cont=
aining three core microservices running on EC2 with Auto Scaling, backed by=
 Amazon Aurora and connected to the NSE exchange via AWS Direct Connect.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"99f3a3a281ba"></p>
<p local-id=3D"644f1f77060f"><strong>[ AWS Cloud Architecture =E2=80=94 Dha=
n Trading Platform]</strong></p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wra=
pper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"co=
nfluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"Untitled Diagram (1)-20260325-=
092454.gif" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"577295265f7a23f793f96a612=
f59441bd8f8e41b448096de72c39a64a3323459" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.a=
tlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1894907934/Untitled%20Diagram%20(1)-=
20260325-092454.gif?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1774532532118&amp;ca=
cheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"1311" data-width=3D"2731" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1904803882" data-=
linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data=
-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Untitled Diagram (1)-20260325-092454.gif"=
 data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-c=
ontent-type=3D"image/gif" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1894907934" =
data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" data-media-id=3D"3b09a244-5ac9=
-401c-ad69-20cb518ffedd" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"224"></span>
<h2 local-id=3D"b677a15bf561" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-3.2CoreAWSServicesUsed">3.2 Core AWS =
Services Used</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2a433e7e664a"><strong>Networking &amp; Traffic Management</s=
trong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ed5832c02d27">
<li local-id=3D"c3172e29b466">
<p local-id=3D"3a88e2708dff"><strong>Amazon Route 53</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"869d25820e7f">DNS resolution for client requests with health=
-check routing and latency-based policies.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"da706a2cf587">
<li local-id=3D"e6e260f2d44c">
<p local-id=3D"9a003a2adacf"><strong>AWS API Gateway</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3e08920ca987">Handles authentication, request routing, throt=
tling, and low-latency ingress for all client API calls.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"81caba1e1487">
<li local-id=3D"6d5745b91ea0">
<p local-id=3D"f6845e9b1329"><strong>AWS Direct Connect</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a3ef9c07089d">Dedicated private network link (bypassing the =
public internet) from the AWS VPC to the on-prem co-location router and NSE=
 exchange.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c2435a701fd0"><strong>Compute</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"dca9f2761f65">
<li local-id=3D"c90f9b1345c7">
<p local-id=3D"af0b036d488d"><strong>Amazon EC2 with Auto Scaling Groups</s=
trong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8a2613254f34">Three core microservices run on EC2 instances =
within a private subnet. Each service has its own Auto Scaling Group for in=
dependent horizontal scaling.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ee30131a9d36">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
OMS (Order Management System) =E2=80=94 receives, validates, and routes ord=
ers</p>
<p local-id=3D"45a40337c8b4">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
RMS (Risk Management System) =E2=80=94 enforces real-time margin and risk r=
ules</p>
<p local-id=3D"db2fda19b22e">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
EMS (Execution Management System) =E2=80=94 manages order execution lifecyc=
le and logs</p>
<p local-id=3D"c382f870569f"><strong>Database</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"cf3f275ec398">
<li local-id=3D"056f00c4afd5">
<p local-id=3D"4f0fcc7207d7"><strong>Amazon Aurora (PostgreSQL-compatible)<=
/strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f59f754e5077">Multi-AZ Aurora cluster with &lt;20ms replicat=
ion latency and &lt;1 minute failover. Stores orders, risk data, execution =
logs, and user account state.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1226523703a9"><strong>AI &amp; Intelligence</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"e932efbbab7a">
<li local-id=3D"2cf380b5b9a6">
<p local-id=3D"3ab53bb28475"><strong>Amazon Bedrock</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5ac958b43446">Used for AI-powered features such as intellige=
nt customer support, portfolio analytics, and anomaly detection in trading =
patterns.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ff5345a39a6a"><strong>Operations &amp; Automation</strong></=
p>
<ul local-id=3D"f62b06ce9939">
<li local-id=3D"d269db884983">
<p local-id=3D"b2696e991340"><strong>AWS Systems Manager</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"30cede520c6e">Centralized patch management, remote command e=
xecution on EC2 fleets, and ops automation without SSH.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"98692a4c5727">
<li local-id=3D"659050074341">
<p local-id=3D"2dcd679b020c"><strong>AWS Lambda</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"99d7c52b5f97">Event-driven serverless functions for alert pr=
ocessing, compliance workflow triggers, and batch reporting tasks.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c012f60539cf"><strong>Observability &amp; Security</strong><=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"612e40f23068">
<li local-id=3D"10e7f865804c">
<p local-id=3D"2d83d2e57abd"><strong>Amazon CloudWatch</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4ba5de5cc8b8">Unified metrics, logs, and alarms. Triggers La=
mbda functions on threshold breaches for automated incident response.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b55560880683">
<li local-id=3D"474411037587">
<p local-id=3D"5ea297eb9ab1"><strong>AWS Security Hub</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"363dff006c89">Aggregates security findings from all AWS serv=
ices. Provides continuous vulnerability assessment, compliance checks (CIS,=
 PCI-DSS), and integrated alerting.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d2cba590793b">&nbsp;</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"ee81f7a7d14e" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-3.3High-LevelDataFlow">3.3 High-Level=
 Data Flow</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2e0e0967451f">
<li local-id=3D"4fe2997374dd">
<p local-id=3D"4221bd9908dd">User sends DNS query =E2=86=92 Route 53 resolv=
es to API Gateway endpoint</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"2" local-id=3D"560ebcaee40f">
<li local-id=3D"18a8f9eda452">
<p local-id=3D"1867759de075">API Gateway authenticates request and routes t=
o load balancer in public subnet</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"3" local-id=3D"586c2d5405f0">
<li local-id=3D"131da7a68d8c">
<p local-id=3D"43405cf1427f">Load balancer forwards HTTP/HTTPS traffic to O=
MS EC2 instances in private subnet</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"4" local-id=3D"7401939a7549">
<li local-id=3D"222b5c77d439">
<p local-id=3D"12ea30623c73">OMS validates order and calls RMS for real-tim=
e risk check</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"5" local-id=3D"49e158399d1f">
<li local-id=3D"ba490f038f17">
<p local-id=3D"1a14a99a1d46">Approved orders are written to Aurora and forw=
arded to EMS</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"6" local-id=3D"3c503536744d">
<li local-id=3D"cedf839b2d54">
<p local-id=3D"59ab449f7bb5">EMS routes the order to NSE via AWS Direct Con=
nect / on-prem router</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"7" local-id=3D"72029e487683">
<li local-id=3D"2031b6e76f5c">
<p local-id=3D"60ab3b04cbda">Execution logs flow back into Aurora; CloudWat=
ch monitors all metrics</p></li>
</ol>
<ol start=3D"8" local-id=3D"b40b3e34bd33">
<li local-id=3D"5d5a2fd1f729">
<p local-id=3D"ebe1c28c9b78">Security Hub continuously scans all layers; La=
mbda fires alerts automatically</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"e2c99f2d6674">&nbsp;</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"537c3e7f6da0" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-3.4Scalability,Availability&amp;Secur=
ity">3.4 Scalability, Availability &amp; Security</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"1c7cb04f691c">
<li local-id=3D"d579c8e89eca">
<p local-id=3D"e2abb3f22251">Scalability: Auto Scaling Groups allow OMS, RM=
S, and EMS to scale independently based on CPU/memory thresholds, handling =
peak market-open traffic spikes.</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"cc1d40d4e2be">
<li local-id=3D"7ebcc2120ce8">
<p local-id=3D"925b81f27dec">Availability: Aurora Multi-AZ provides &lt;1 m=
in failover. EC2 instances span multiple AZs. Direct Connect has redundant =
links.</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"df4e260c8f48">
<li local-id=3D"48dbd2cb8b2c">
<p local-id=3D"809b7c96c84f">Security: API Gateway enforces auth/throttling=
. VPC isolates compute. Security Hub + CloudWatch provide 24x7 monitoring, =
automated alerting, and compliance reporting for SEBI mandates.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8733a6f1cb0c">&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"6983c1e1ecc3">&nbsp;</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"5a688489fad4" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-4.On-PremiseAlternativeArchitecture(O=
pen-SourceOnly)">4. On-Premise Alternative Architecture (Open-Source Only)<=
/h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"09d6ba98e04c" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-4.1DesignPhilosophy">4.1 Design Philo=
sophy</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9eed9b7a7531">The on-prem alternative replicates the same fu=
nctional layers as the AWS design =E2=80=94 network routing, compute, datab=
ases, observability, and security =E2=80=94 using exclusively open-source t=
ools deployed on bare-metal or virtualized hardware within a private data c=
enter.&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"bf484feaee10"><strong>[ On-Premise Open-Source Architecture =
=E2=80=94 Dhan Trading Platform ]</strong></p><span class=3D"confluence-emb=
edded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><i=
mg class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"Untitled asdfg-2=
0260326-133258.gif" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"40231ceb7f1be5e33=
766b4c8395abfb1ed950a37542b13aba5d2de82e999b960" data-image-src=3D"https://=
iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1894907934/Untitled%20asdfg-=
20260326-133258.gif?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1774532584209&amp;ca=
cheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"892" data-width=3D"1851" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1904803889" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Untitled asdfg-20260326-133258.gif" data-b=
ase-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-=
type=3D"image/gif" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1894907934" data-li=
nked-resource-container-version=3D"3" data-media-id=3D"65d179f2-218c-4b09-9=
698-5ea598f8a26e" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"225"></span>
<p local-id=3D"12a05dcebbc3"></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"98a4f40840e2" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-4.2ComponentBreakdown">4.2 Component =
Breakdown</h2>
<p local-id=3D"af916d622b2d"><strong>DNS Resolution</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ad7a60f87de9">
<li local-id=3D"e9e72a0da997">
<p local-id=3D"624ae4157b32">Tool: BIND 9</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4d234eba0b20">BIND 9 is the industry-standard open-source DN=
S server. It handles all internal and external DNS queries, replacing Route=
 53. Zone files are managed locally with health-check scripting via externa=
l tools.</p>
<p local-id=3D"761403d5eff8"><strong>API Gateway / Traffic Ingress</strong>=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"1f0c4f7aa436">
<li local-id=3D"45d9ef68dfdf">
<p local-id=3D"27a08f9e2ba7">Tool: NGINX / Kong (open-source edition)</p></=
li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"aa6491e7dfd5">NGINX acts as a reverse proxy and API gateway,=
 handling authentication (JWT/OAuth), rate limiting, routing, and SSL termi=
nation. Kong provides a plugin-based gateway layer for more advanced API ma=
nagement needs.</p>
<p local-id=3D"46a7637e1d1f"><strong>Load Balancer</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"771a27fbd361">
<li local-id=3D"7fa1862f42fe">
<p local-id=3D"90c732567d8a">Tool: HAProxy / NGINX</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"04f7611b907a">HAProxy provides high-performance TCP and HTTP=
 load balancing across application server instances. It supports health che=
cks, sticky sessions, and weighted routing =E2=80=94 equivalent to an AWS A=
LB/NLB.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0212a1ef0c61"><strong>Compute / Application Servers</strong>=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5352cde5c450">
<li local-id=3D"6bc4faa8a81b">
<p local-id=3D"caba26986e3e">Tool: Kubernetes (K3s / kubeadm) on KVM VMs or=
 bare metal</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"70e34f705e81">The three microservices (OMS, RMS, EMS) are co=
ntainerized and deployed as Kubernetes pods. Kubernetes manages scheduling,=
 auto-scaling (HPA), self-healing, and rolling deployments =E2=80=94 replac=
ing EC2 Auto Scaling Groups.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0c2e9539fb46">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
OMS Pods =E2=80=94 order intake, validation, and routing</p>
<p local-id=3D"59f65c9fb7f0">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
RMS Pods =E2=80=94 risk checks, margin enforcement</p>
<p local-id=3D"99b336d2ead5">=E2=97=A6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =
EMS Pods =E2=80=94 execution lifecycle, trade confirmation</p>
<p local-id=3D"d0688499b5ef"><strong>Database</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"f036886425ca">
<li local-id=3D"6722de3e983a">
<p local-id=3D"16f19dadb929">Tool: PostgreSQL with Patroni (HA) + replicati=
on</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"72d0053a71d2">PostgreSQL with Patroni provides a high-availa=
bility cluster with automatic leader election and failover (equivalent to A=
urora Multi-AZ). Streaming replication ensures low-latency replicas for rea=
d scaling.</p>
<p local-id=3D"99109f10b56b"><strong>Messaging &amp; Event Processing</stro=
ng></p>
<ul local-id=3D"c94829b2856b">
<li local-id=3D"56bb5e4f8626">
<p local-id=3D"645bb4304813">Tool: Apache Kafka / RabbitMQ</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cbb4bacdf086">Kafka handles high-throughput event streaming =
between services (order events, execution logs, risk updates). It replaces =
the event-driven Lambda + CloudWatch Alarms pattern. RabbitMQ is used for s=
impler task queues.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b100c712cff7"><strong>Batch Processing / Cron Jobs</strong><=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"f18783423813">
<li local-id=3D"4bbdf7529b47">
<p local-id=3D"ac2d7c800b44">Tool: Custom Python workers + Linux cron</p></=
li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2456b9292bca">Cron-based workers handle end-of-day batch job=
s, compliance report generation, alert dispatching, and data export tasks =
=E2=80=94 replacing AWS Lambda for scheduled/event-driven workloads.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6f3df4c31bf4"><strong>Logging Stack</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"c762cb8e6743">
<li local-id=3D"9fb6e83add98">
<p local-id=3D"338ab889b4c7">Tool: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch + Logstash + Ki=
bana)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5e0ab2030988">Logstash ingests and parses logs from all appl=
ication pods and system components. Elasticsearch indexes and stores them. =
Kibana provides dashboards for log search and operational queries =E2=80=94=
 equivalent to CloudWatch Logs Insights.</p>
<p local-id=3D"db8e4fda7b04"><strong>Monitoring &amp; Alerting</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"42b8bf540f84">
<li local-id=3D"236b64fe397d">
<p local-id=3D"77b5bc866dcb">Tool: Prometheus + Grafana + Alertmanager</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"479f0fb974ea">Prometheus scrapes metrics from all Kubernetes=
 pods and host nodes. Grafana renders dashboards and trend graphs. Alertman=
ager routes alerts to email, Slack, or PagerDuty =E2=80=94 replacing CloudW=
atch Metrics + Alarms.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ec82be268f13"><strong>Security Monitoring &amp; Compliance</=
strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"f0ba7f61d3ae">
<li local-id=3D"00104bde515c">
<p local-id=3D"fc4fb406628c">Tool: Wazuh + OpenVAS</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"fbfa75301941">Wazuh provides SIEM (Security Information and =
Event Management), intrusion detection, file integrity monitoring, and comp=
liance checks (PCI-DSS, CIS). OpenVAS handles continuous vulnerability scan=
ning =E2=80=94 together replacing AWS Security Hub.</p>
<p local-id=3D"01cbc144c40f"><strong>Configuration Management &amp; Deploym=
ent</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"290751b7ea86">
<li local-id=3D"96cd756709cc">
<p local-id=3D"1ee0d1dcd170">Tool: Ansible + SSH</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ffee790a482c">Ansible playbooks automate server provisioning=
, configuration management, patch deployment, and application rollouts =E2=
=80=94 replacing AWS Systems Manager.</p>
<p local-id=3D"46efa5dedaa0"><strong>Exchange Connectivity</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"885b9a4e6843">
<li local-id=3D"cd1d2d4630a9">
<p local-id=3D"3ebb24286549">Tool: Dedicated leased line / MPLS link =E2=86=
=92 on-prem router =E2=86=92 NSE</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e3aa410bc461">A dedicated low-latency network link (leased l=
ine or dark fiber) connects the data center to the exchange co-location. Th=
is replaces AWS Direct Connect. The on-prem router manages BGP routing and =
failover.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b5a1cb0504df">&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"74cefeb20ec6">&nbsp;</p>
