<h1 local-id=3D"aa0ee855d815" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-6.Comparison:AWSvs.On-PremiseOpen-Sou=
rce">6. Comparison: AWS vs. On-Premise Open-Source</h1>
<p local-id=3D"64991c5d926c">&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a=
6d127ab-e3be-49db-97f4-60ca9d27413b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"f3539188980b">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#0d2e5c" data-local-id=3D"94a10a68f09d" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c34bd70ca45e"><strong>Dimension</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#0d2e5c" data-local-id=3D"7a4c77dbf630" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8b059d8d2d27"><strong>AWS-Based Design</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#0d2e5c" data-local-id=3D"d1fe32485975" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"113449fb8363"><strong>On-Prem Open-Source Design</strong></p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"8e6dc27b9db8">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"2b55d387712d" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e714378be340"><strong>Cost Model</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"abc0e8ed83fa" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"553ee71a3340">OpEx: pay-per-use. Scales with usage. Can be e=
xpensive at high throughput. No upfront hardware cost.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"049be07d35d0" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9f94156b1570">CapEx: large upfront hardware investment. Lowe=
r unit cost at sustained high volume. Power, cooling, and DC costs ongoing.=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"611002c91248">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"1a80a541f413" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eb300d7511b6"><strong>Scalability</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"0f5fd2070ad7" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6c344ea0ab40">Near-infinite horizontal scaling. Auto Scaling=
 Groups provision new instances in minutes. Multi-region globally.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"97bd1d647a26" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c71827ed74a8">Limited by data center capacity. Kubernetes HP=
A scales pods quickly, but adding physical nodes takes days. Vertical scali=
ng has limits.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3f178b0bd6f3">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"ebdee56ee948" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"279e55158c12"><strong>Operational Effort</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"cdc94e29ee10" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a08ac92d02d1">Low ops overhead. AWS manages infrastructure, =
patching, HA failover, and hardware failures automatically.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"00878be3b87b" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6f13922f342f">High ops burden. Team must manage hardware fai=
lures, OS patching, network configuration, and HA setup manually.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d75f93f487d7">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"8f257bb6db0c" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5bdeb14cd480"><strong>Control &amp; Sovereignty</strong></p>=
</td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"36d2631c602f" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c723857bda53">AWS owns the underlying infrastructure. Limite=
d control over hypervisor, networking hardware, and physical security.</p><=
/td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"0c42801827ac" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7c14d5052dd0">Full control over hardware, software stack, da=
ta, and network. Critical for regulated financial data and SEBI compliance =
requirements.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6407454b259d">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"a7fe649b8a9d" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"045eff345b02"><strong>Reliability / HA</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"c63a45d2380f" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7bdf02d443f6">Multi-AZ by default. SLAs up to 99.99%. Automa=
ted failover for Aurora, EC2, and networking.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"b42992f9d77f" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"17281cb9d45c">HA requires careful design (Patroni, Keepalive=
d, redundant links). Failover takes more effort to configure and test.</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ef3dc56969ab">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"93b6da72e3cb" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"15ec94c39ec8"><strong>Security</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"570c23afb434" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b2ba974a38cf">AWS manages physical and hypervisor-layer secu=
rity. Security Hub provides automated compliance reporting.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"0687fcbc3280" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4389b420c8f7">Team owns end-to-end security. Wazuh + OpenVAS=
 provide strong SIEM/scanning, but require dedicated security engineers.</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"330d4d63e613">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"b55449370999" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d8dcf5811de2"><strong>Time to Deploy</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"79f2fd9dc63b" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"092c6685dfe8">Infra can be provisioned in hours with IaC (Te=
rraform, CDK). New environments spin up quickly.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"3a962e27843c" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"728e67d1eb47">Procurement and rack-up of physical hardware c=
an take weeks. Software deployment via Ansible is fast once hardware is rea=
dy.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"437795c8c1a2">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"d38bf1cd0b53" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7d1d716ee07e"><strong>Vendor Lock-in</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"396cf66e67f0" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"29da166ccbaf">Moderate-high lock-in to AWS services (Aurora,=
 Bedrock, Direct Connect APIs, IAM integrations).</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"ed4cf2a5c7fb" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"220ce9ac8a7f">No vendor lock-in. All tools are open standard=
s. Easier to migrate or swap components independently.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"370ebab6eef2">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"b3daca711cc3" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b6716bc80b75"><strong>Latency to Exchange</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"1e745cf09838" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"24125936639f">Direct Connect provides dedicated low-latency =
link, but still routes through AWS edge infrastructure.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"f198ca16ba65" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e08a5f4795e4">Co-location with direct leased-line can achiev=
e lower latency than cloud. On-prem is preferred for true HFT use cases.</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"493db4046b80">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#f2f2f2" data-local-id=3D"9baa4b4ab1fc" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"706b5f48aaa1"><strong>Disaster Recovery</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"4099079be769" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d5e555f9d9da">Cross-region replication is trivially enabled.=
 S3 and Aurora support point-in-time recovery natively.</p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"white" data-local-id=3D"03993a4da9f0" class=3D=
"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"249e465693aa">DR requires a secondary DC. Replication must b=
e configured manually. Recovery procedures are more complex to automate.</p=
></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"57fa0e001754">&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"6d727934914e">&nbsp;</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"2dc93b5b4ab5" id=3D"Task25-ResearchingAWSArchitectureandDes=
igninganOpen-SourceOn-PremAlternative-7.Recommendation&amp;Conclusion">7. R=
ecommendation &amp; Conclusion</h1>
<p local-id=3D"3463b1391b14">Both architectures are viable for a trading pl=
atform like Dhan. The right choice depends on ABC Technologies' priorities:=
</p>
<p local-id=3D"8858f87d04f9">&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5=
8cde782-a3b1-44b2-a551-8490666e1cc3" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a5a1410f5862">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#1f497d" data-local-id=3D"65d94b03963e" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1d74e8bd4aac"><strong>Choose AWS If...</strong></p></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#e07b20" data-local-id=3D"f25f3e3df5cd" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6b112520e99f"><strong>Choose On-Prem If...</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9f2d46bcb180">
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#d6e4f0" data-local-id=3D"36150aa34887" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul local-id=3D"96291ab93db3">
<li local-id=3D"88a8930c9a8d">
<p local-id=3D"e2ddb017df2a">You need fast time-to-market</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"742da13d8088">
<li local-id=3D"4c810b3b3013">
<p local-id=3D"b0e2d278a6cd">Engineering team is small and ops capacity is =
limited</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"2fa1bbcf06e4">
<li local-id=3D"af1534ecb34c">
<p local-id=3D"ebff930fcd58">Traffic is unpredictable and needs elastic sca=
ling</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"46283c866fbb">
<li local-id=3D"3b1e6825c997">
<p local-id=3D"39ac4ceec7c0">Multi-region global availability is required</=
p></li>
</ul></td>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#fff0e0" data-local-id=3D"ddb7985dbc9f" class=
=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul local-id=3D"500b35a62428">
<li local-id=3D"5ec3ae83ca2d">
<p local-id=3D"b36893fec460">Data sovereignty and regulatory compliance dem=
and on-prem hosting</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"a10cd29d2661">
<li local-id=3D"efcde0dab780">
<p local-id=3D"df07f94fdfac">Ultra-low latency to exchange is critical (tru=
e HFT)</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"308e213cd890">
<li local-id=3D"39dea46b85f0">
<p local-id=3D"ca858a4cbb3b">You have a strong DevOps/infra team and prefer=
 full control</p></li>
</ul>
<ul local-id=3D"e3ec89331083">
<li local-id=3D"957bbe5008eb">
<p local-id=3D"7ce79b1fcfee">Long-term cost savings at high sustained throu=
ghput matter most</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"de29e87b5f43">&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"73b28cb544c0">For a trading platform like Dhan operating in =
India, a hybrid approach is most pragmatic =E2=80=94 on-prem co-location fo=
r exchange connectivity and order execution (to minimize latency), with AWS=
 for non-latency-sensitive services like analytics, customer portals, AI fe=
atures, and compliance reporting.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f3affd9b9a39">&nbsp;</p>
<p local-id=3D"c2e2afef2b5d">&nbsp;</p>
